File written. Here is what it contains and why each section is built the way it is:

/home/toby/jag-electric-site/agency-handoffs/sage-brand.md

---

WHAT GOT BUILT:

**Remembered moment** — The two-beat circuit board mechanic is named and locked: service area glows first, estimate-prep panel second. That is the brand story in motion form.

**Visual fingerprint** — Switchgear-black, copper trace texture at 8-12% opacity, cyan glow that activates rather than decorates, amber as a caution signal not a brand color. Named the specific anti-pattern: orange is not amber, and the site will not look like the contractor template the brief explicitly banned.

**Color tokens** — Full CSS custom property system with hex values and OKLCH for every surface, glow, amber, and copper tier. Usage rules are written so Craig can't accidentally use amber as a background or cyan as a solid fill.

**Typography** — Barlow Condensed 800 for display (panel labels, not marketing soft-speak), Inter for body, JetBrains Mono for technical labels and estimate output. That third tier is what makes the estimate workbench feel like a real panel form rather than a generic textarea.

**Section design rules** — 11 rules covering nav, hero, trust bar, services (panel-schedule row layout, not card grid — that was the specific brief instruction), circuit-area map, reviews, estimate-prep workbench, about, service pages, city pages, and footer. Each rule names exact token references and calls out forbidden shortcuts.

**Logo direction** — Bolt icon + condensed wordmark, two wordmark color options, four variants (primary, reversed, mono, favicon), and a rejection list so no fleet-truck decal or cartoon spark sneaks through.

**Asset inventory** — 13 slots with IDs, page assignments, and explicit status: circuit map and estimate workbench are BUILD, Joe Gendre photo is PLACEHOLDER with a hard prohibition on generating a stock electrician and labeling it as him, review cards are APPROVED/COPY-VERIFIED from the brief.

**Forbidden list** — Specific rejected imagery (robotic arms, holographic circuits, blue-orange gradient), forbidden language (24/7, same-day guarantee, license numbers, fake form sends), and forbidden design patterns (three-column card grid, orange accent, white backgrounds).

**Motion language** — Circuit trace stroke-dashoffset animation, 60fps desktop with graceful mobile fallback, estimate panel typewriter reveal, `prefers-reduced-motion` handled. No parallax on mobile.

**Design gate checklist** — 17 checkboxes Forge/Craig must pass before any page is accepted. Covers route depth, truth constraints, and both desktop and mobile visual inspection.
